<br />Okay, now there's other things I'd like to know. 
<br />
<br />1) How long is the time, in CPU cycles, between the end of rendering one scanline and the start of rendering the next (aka HBlank)? 
<br />
<br />2) I've read that the MMC3 interrupts can be triggered up to 7 CPU cycles before the scanline ends. How long should I delay before I start writing to the PPU? 
<br />
<br />3) I notice that in many demos, there's "shearing" between scanlines where mid-frame scroling takes place. What can be done to prevent ths? I read somewhere that you can't scroll more than 8 pixels without shearing, citing Chris Covell's CMCWavy demo. I was also thinking I could have certain scanlines where I do scrolling solid colors, but I don't know which scanline would shear (the one before or after the HBlank scroll).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

